On September 29, 2017, the President signed two laws related to veterans and education. The first law, H.R. 3819, extends certain expiring authorities affecting veterans and their families. This includes healthcare, benefits, homelessness, and other miscellaneous authorities. The law also makes technical corrections. The second law, S. 1866, provides the Department of Education with administrative authority to assist institutions of higher education affected by recent hurricanes and tropical storms. It also establishes a grant program to provide equitable services to children and teachers in private schools.